org.ontouml.model.Class
public class Class extends Classifier<Class,ClassStereotype>
A classifier that defines the properties of a set of "individualized" entities (i.e., non-relational) of the subject domain. Examples include "Person", "Enrollment", and "Grade". The instances of a class may include entities such as objects (e.g., people, organizations, vehicles), reified properties (e.g., leafs' colors, agents' intentions, enrollments), and bare values (e.g., a number or a literal).
